You do it lovingly.

00:54:01.780 --> 00:54:03.330 align:middle line:90%
You enjoy it.

00:54:03.330 --> 00:54:05.470 align:middle line:90%
We're not here to suffer.

00:54:05.470 --> 00:54:10.660 align:middle line:84%
There is a beautiful
mantra, Om Namah Shivaya.

00:54:10.660 --> 00:54:11.880 align:middle line:90%
Nothing is mine.

00:54:11.880 --> 00:54:13.120 align:middle line:90%
Everything is thine.

00:54:13.120 --> 00:54:16.230 align:middle line:84%
Everything is here for
me to use and enjoy

00:54:16.230 --> 00:54:20.080 align:middle line:84%
but not to possess
nor be possessed by.

00:54:20.080 --> 00:54:22.990 align:middle line:84%
So we are here,
Om Namah Shivaya,

00:54:22.990 --> 00:54:28.590 align:middle line:84%
to live this beautiful place
we've all manifest into.

00:54:28.590 --> 00:54:31.370 align:middle line:90%
How lucky are we?

00:54:31.370 --> 00:54:34.280 align:middle line:84%
And how lucky are we to
have people in our lives

00:54:34.280 --> 00:54:38.020 align:middle line:90%
to love and to care with?

00:54:38.020 --> 00:54:41.390 align:middle line:84%
>>It really all comes
back to being about love.

00:54:41.390 --> 00:54:43.100 align:middle line:90%
Everything is based in love.

00:54:43.100 --> 00:54:45.070 align:middle line:84%
And we separate
ourselves from it.

00:54:45.070 --> 00:54:47.895 align:middle line:84%
Our ego's job is to kind
of keep us separate.

00:54:47.895 --> 00:54:50.200 align:middle line:84%
As I'm trying to come
to the understanding

00:54:50.200 --> 00:54:53.090 align:middle line:84%
that I'm really not
separate, the ego's

00:54:53.090 --> 00:54:55.790 align:middle line:84%
apt to freak out, give
me all kinds of reasons

00:54:55.790 --> 00:54:57.819 align:middle line:90%
to believe that I'm separate.

00:54:57.819 --> 00:54:58.610 align:middle line:90%
Well, look at this.

00:54:58.610 --> 00:54:59.320 align:middle line:90%
Look at that.

00:54:59.320 --> 00:55:00.120 align:middle line:90%
Of course you're separate.

00:55:00.120 --> 00:55:00.620 align:middle line:90%
You're separate.

00:55:00.620 --> 00:55:01.203 align:middle line:90%
You're unique.

00:55:01.203 --> 00:55:03.410 align:middle line:90%
You're distinct, whatever.

00:55:03.410 --> 00:55:09.660 align:middle line:84%
And my soul is striving through
all of this to reach oneness.

00:55:09.660 --> 00:55:13.360 align:middle line:84%
My ego is having the
opportunity to morph,

00:55:13.360 --> 00:55:14.910 align:middle line:90%
to take on a different job.

00:55:14.910 --> 00:55:16.560 align:middle line:84%
I've asked my ego
if it wouldn't like

00:55:16.560 --> 00:55:23.360 align:middle line:84%
to help me to remember
that I'm part of the whole

00:55:23.360 --> 00:55:27.240 align:middle line:84%
rather than needing
to be separate.

00:55:27.240 --> 00:55:29.340 align:middle line:90%
>>What is it that you believe?

00:55:29.340 --> 00:55:31.000 align:middle line:84%
What were you taught
as a young child

00:55:31.000 --> 00:55:32.890 align:middle line:90%
about what happens when you die?

00:55:32.890 --> 00:55:35.660 align:middle line:84%
Do you still carry
those same beliefs?

00:55:35.660 --> 00:55:37.900 align:middle line:90%
Or have they changed?

00:55:37.900 --> 00:55:40.780 align:middle line:84%
Many people rely on
religion or beliefs

00:55:40.780 --> 00:55:44.680 align:middle line:84%
to help understand where
the soul goes when it dies.

00:55:44.680 --> 00:55:47.410 align:middle line:84%
Many of us hold
onto those beliefs.

00:55:47.410 --> 00:55:50.290 align:middle line:84%
However, can these
beliefs sometimes

00:55:50.290 --> 00:55:54.190 align:middle line:84%
limit us from exploring
other possibilities

00:55:54.190 --> 00:55:57.230 align:middle line:90%
as to what happens when we die?

00:55:57.230 --> 00:55:59.460 align:middle line:84%
>>Seminary was a
process of dismantling

00:55:59.460 --> 00:56:00.580 align:middle line:90%
a lot of my beliefs.

00:56:00.580 --> 00:56:05.350 align:middle line:84%
Before I went to seminary, I had
my beliefs pretty well in mind.

00:56:05.350 --> 00:56:09.390 align:middle line:84%
I usually say that my
story begins in many ways

00:56:09.390 --> 00:56:12.780 align:middle line:84%
when I fell off of the roof
of an underground house.

00:56:12.780 --> 00:56:15.030 align:middle line:90%
This was back in the 1970s.

00:56:15.030 --> 00:56:17.620 align:middle line:84%
And my brother and I had
a construction company.

00:56:17.620 --> 00:56:20.130 align:middle line:84%
And this was the
first energy crisis.

00:56:20.130 --> 00:56:23.000 align:middle line:84%
And so people were exploring
all kinds of different ways

00:56:23.000 --> 00:56:27.260 align:middle line:84%
to save energy in building
and in cars and whatnot.

00:56:27.260 --> 00:56:30.000 align:middle line:84%
So my brother and I thought
that underground houses

00:56:30.000 --> 00:56:32.720 align:middle line:90%
were the wave of the future.

00:56:32.720 --> 00:56:35.990 align:middle line:84%
And one day we were
building a home.

00:56:35.990 --> 00:56:37.380 align:middle line:90%
They're made out of concrete.

00:56:37.380 --> 00:56:38.900 align:middle line:90%
And I was up on top of the roof.

00:56:38.900 --> 00:56:41.970 align:middle line:84%
And we had just poured
the concrete roof.

00:56:41.970 --> 00:56:43.790 align:middle line:84%
And I was pulling
on a form board.

00:56:43.790 --> 00:56:45.290 align:middle line:84%
And all of a
sudden, it gave way.

00:56:45.290 --> 00:56:48.060 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself
falling off of the roof.

00:56:48.060 --> 00:56:52.030 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't even have any
time to adjust to the fall.

00:56:52.030 --> 00:56:54.430 align:middle line:84%
And I slammed into
a pile of gravel.

00:56:54.430 --> 00:56:55.970 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know
it at the time.

00:56:55.970 --> 00:56:58.260 align:middle line:84%
But I ended up
fracturing my hip.

00:56:58.260 --> 00:57:00.620 align:middle line:90%
They put me in physical therapy.

00:57:00.620 --> 00:57:03.370 align:middle line:84%
And I found out that, when
I was in physical therapy,

00:57:03.370 --> 00:57:05.060 align:middle line:84%
that I was in
extraordinary pain.

00:57:05.060 --> 00:57:06.477 align:middle line:84%
And so the doctor
came by one day.

00:57:06.477 --> 00:57:08.643 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at me and
said, you're really hurting,

00:57:08.643 --> 00:57:09.160 align:middle line:90%
aren't you?

00:57:09.160 --> 00:57:10.090 align:middle line:90%
And I said, yeah.

00:57:10.090 --> 00:57:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, let's take
some more x-rays of that hip.

00:57:13.960 --> 00:57:17.690 align:middle line:84%
And so when they did,
taking at an oblique angle,

00:57:17.690 --> 00:57:19.790 align:middle line:84%
they did find that there
was a fracture there.

00:57:19.790 --> 00:57:21.260 align:middle line:84%
The doctor comes
in and says, I'm

00:57:21.260 --> 00:57:22.940 align:middle line:84%
going to be off
work for six weeks

00:57:22.940 --> 00:57:24.840 align:middle line:90%
and that I would be in traction.

00:57:24.840 --> 00:57:28.420 align:middle line:84%
And so I went into this
spiral of pain and anxiety

00:57:28.420 --> 00:57:32.850 align:middle line:84%
at that time, pain because the
hip was pretty excruciating.

00:57:32.850 --> 00:57:37.900 align:middle line:84%
So I just kind of went
spiraling downward.

00:57:37.900 --> 00:57:40.670 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
I popped through

00:57:40.670 --> 00:57:43.760 align:middle line:84%
into an entirely
different reality.

00:57:43.760 --> 00:57:47.450 align:middle line:84%
And in this reality, all of
the pain that I had in my hip

00:57:47.450 --> 00:57:49.155 align:middle line:90%
completely disappeared.

00:57:49.155 --> 00:57:51.470 align:middle line:90%
The anxiety evaporated.

00:57:51.470 --> 00:57:56.110 align:middle line:84%
I found myself surrounded
by complete peace.

00:57:56.110 --> 00:57:58.520 align:middle line:84%
After awhile, I
was also standing

00:57:58.520 --> 00:57:59.970 align:middle line:90%
in front of this being of light.

00:57:59.970 --> 00:58:04.220 align:middle line:84%
And we were conversing
about my life without words.

00:58:04.220 --> 00:58:06.370 align:middle line:84%
And I came out of that
experience so stunned.

00:58:06.370 --> 00:58:10.330 align:middle line:84%
Because I had no idea
that another reality like

00:58:10.330 --> 00:58:13.630 align:middle line:84%
that even existed,
much less the idea

00:58:13.630 --> 00:58:16.490 align:middle line:84%
that you might be
able to experience it.

00:58:16.490 --> 00:58:18.920 align:middle line:84%
Well, I had been
wrestling with an issue of

00:58:18.920 --> 00:58:20.960 align:middle line:84%
whether or not I
should go to seminary.

00:58:20.960 --> 00:58:23.589 align:middle line:84%
Because I really felt
a call to the ministry.

00:58:23.589 --> 00:58:25.130 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, my
immediate reaction

00:58:25.130 --> 00:58:26.630 align:middle line:84%
was, well, this is
the voice of God.

00:58:26.630 --> 00:58:28.530 align:middle line:90%
And I need to go into seminary.

00:58:28.530 --> 00:58:31.640 align:middle line:84%
So I took my wife and, at
that time, two children.

00:58:31.640 --> 00:58:35.190 align:middle line:84%
And we went to Princeton
Theological Seminary.

00:58:35.190 --> 00:58:37.690 align:middle line:84%
And I went through the
three years of training

00:58:37.690 --> 00:58:39.770 align:middle line:84%
to get my Master's Degree
there and then became

00:58:39.770 --> 00:58:42.750 align:middle line:90%
a Presbyterian pastor.

00:58:42.750 --> 00:58:44.530 align:middle line:84%
But as the years
went on, I began

00:58:44.530 --> 00:58:47.310 align:middle line:84%
to realize that the real
purpose of that experience

00:58:47.310 --> 00:58:49.530 align:middle line:84%
was to give me a
taste of something

00:58:49.530 --> 00:58:53.780 align:middle line:84%
and to create a hunger for
something that I knew that

00:58:53.780 --> 00:58:56.130 align:middle line:84%
deep down in my bones
that I had to understand

00:58:56.130 --> 00:58:58.160 align:middle line:90%
and to explore more fully.

00:58:58.160 --> 00:59:00.520 align:middle line:90%
That hunger was so intense.

00:59:00.520 --> 00:59:03.250 align:middle line:84%
It was even more intensified
as I went into the ministry

00:59:03.250 --> 00:59:06.910 align:middle line:84%
because there weren't a lot
of people who were speaking

00:59:06.910 --> 00:59:09.910 align:middle line:84%
about that kind of thing,
at least in my church.

00:59:09.910 --> 00:59:15.130 align:middle line:84%
And so I found myself in this
state of tension, if you will,

00:59:15.130 --> 00:59:17.750 align:middle line:84%
between where I
really wanted to go

00:59:17.750 --> 00:59:19.870 align:middle line:84%
and what I really
wanted to explore

00:59:19.870 --> 00:59:23.910 align:middle line:84%
and the appearances
that I had to keep up

00:59:23.910 --> 00:59:25.720 align:middle line:90%
in my role as a pastor.

00:59:25.720 --> 00:59:28.250 align:middle line:84%
I went into what was then
called the world's largest

00:59:28.250 --> 00:59:30.400 align:middle line:90%
bookstore in Toronto, Canada.

00:59:30.400 --> 00:59:32.210 align:middle line:84%
And when you go into
this place, there

00:59:32.210 --> 00:59:34.550 align:middle line:84%
are books just as far
as the eye can see.

00:59:34.550 --> 00:59:37.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, literally
millions of books.

00:59:37.660 --> 00:59:39.150 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't in there
but two minutes

00:59:39.150 --> 00:59:41.860 align:middle line:84%
when, all of a sudden, one
book jumped off the shelf.

00:59:41.860 --> 00:59:45.470 align:middle line:84%
And it was Bob Monroe's
second book, "Far Journeys."

00:59:45.470 --> 00:59:47.390 align:middle line:84%
When I started
reading that thing,

00:59:47.390 --> 00:59:49.630 align:middle line:84%
I simply couldn't
put the thing down.

00:59:49.630 --> 00:59:51.630 align:middle line:90%
It was so stunning to me.

00:59:51.630 --> 00:59:54.080 align:middle line:84%
Here, for the first
time, was somebody

00:59:54.080 --> 00:59:57.160 align:middle line:84%
who was talking in
a contemporary sense

00:59:57.160 --> 01:00:00.000 align:middle line:84%
about the experience I had
when I fell off the roof.

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:04.020 align:middle line:84%
12 years after I read that
book, I had my first opportunity

01:00:04.020 --> 01:00:07.680 align:middle line:84%
to come to the Monroe Institute
and go through the program

01:00:07.680 --> 01:00:10.070 align:middle line:90%
here, in the Gateway Voyage.

01:00:10.070 --> 01:00:13.710 align:middle line:84%
And to my utter
amazement, that world

01:00:13.710 --> 01:00:16.530 align:middle line:84%
